# Figma Sync

Uses `figma-console-mcp` (Desktop Bridge plugin). Key tools:

| Tool | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `figma_get_selection` | Read selected frame — start any build-component flow here |
| `figma_get_variables` | Extract all design tokens from file |
| `figma_execute` | Run Figma Plugin API code (create, modify, rebind) |
| `figma_take_screenshot` | Capture canvas for visual validation |
| `figma_check_design_parity` | Compare Figma spec against code |
| `figma_batch_create_variables` | Bulk token operations |

## Sync Protocol

1. Design changes are made in Figma first
2. Use `figma_get_selection` + `figma_get_variables` to extract current state
3. `tokens/tokens.json` is updated as source of truth
4. Regenerate `tokens.css`, `tokens.scss`, `tokens.ts`
5. Push back to Figma via `figma_execute` running `figma-sync-4layer.js` functions

## Build Component from Selection

1. Select component frame in Figma (Desktop Bridge running)
2. Call `figma_get_selection` → read frame structure
3. Call `figma_get_variables` → read token bindings
4. Compare against `tokens/tokens.json`
5. Scaffold component with correct token references

## Parity Rule

Token names map 1:1 between Figma variables and CSS custom properties.
